The paper deals with the problem of assessing the stability and resiliency of power grids, which involves analyzing large-scale, strongly nonlinear systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a framework for constructing a robust assessment toolbox, which involves mathematical modeling and optimization, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also mentions the use of quadratic Lyapunov functions, which are commonly used in the field of Neural Networks (cs.NE), and the numerical simulations involve solving optimization problems, which is a common theme in the Optimization and Control (cs.SI) category.
